The article is a transcript of remarks made by President Obama and President Medvedev of Russia prior to a private meeting in Moscow. President Medvedev welcomes President Obama to the Kremlin and expresses his hope for a fruitful discussion on various issues such as economy, security, and strategic offensive armaments. President Obama thanks President Medvedev for his hospitality and expresses confidence in building off previous discussions in London. He emphasizes that the United States and Russia have more in common than differences and that progress during the meetings will benefit both countries. President Medvedev jokes about the weather being chilly outside and suggests working inside. President Obama recalls his previous visit to Moscow when it was 80 degrees.